{{Infobox language |name=Bango |nativename= |region= |states=[[DR Congo]] |ethnicity=[[Babango]] |speakers={{sigfig|2550|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] ([[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C.40]]) |fam6=[[Boan languages|Boan]] |fam7=Bomokandian |fam8=[[Bwa languages (Bantu)|Bwa]] |iso3=bbm |glotto=baba1263 |glottorefname=Babango |guthrie=C.441 }} '''Bango''' (Mobango, Babango), is a [[Bantu language]] spoken in the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]]. ''Ethnologue'' suggests it may be a dialect of [[Budza language|Budza]], but Nurse & Philippson (2003) list it as one of the [[Bati–Angba languages|Bwa languages]].
