{{Organic-chem-stub}}

'''micri''' is an [[archaism|archaic]] non-[[SI]] [[decimal]] [[metric prefix]] for 10<sup>−14</sup>. Its symbol was mc.<ref name="Cardarelli_2003"/>
It was proposed as a prefix for the [[Centimetre–gram–second system of units|CGS]]-unit of energy, the [[erg]]. The name [[micri-erg]] was proposed in 1922 by [[William Draper Harkins]] as a unit of energy equating to 10<sup>−14</sup>&nbsp;erg,<ref name="Cardarelli_2003"/><ref name="Harkins_1922"/><ref name="Colloid_1925"/><ref name="ACh_1922"/><ref name="Jerrard_2012"/><ref name="Partington_1949"/> the equivalent to 10<sup>−21</sup>&nbsp;[[joule]], as a convenient unit to measure the [[surface energy]] of [[molecule]]s<ref name="Jerrard_2012"/> in [[surface chemistry]].<ref name="Cardarelli_1966"/> It only saw limited use.
